      "author_association": "NONE",
      "body": "> Is this a bugfix? If so, how is this bug triggered?\r\n\r\nHello sir, \r\n\r\nThe old condition checks `line_idx < len(lines)`, but then accesses `lines[line_idx + 1]`, which raises `IndexError`.\r\n\r\n while `line_idx + 1 < len(lines) and lines[line_idx + 1] != ''` is a safer condition to check.\r\n \r\n It can be triggered if the helper receives truncated or malformed `bitcoin-cli -getinfo` output where `Balances` is the final line.\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you!! \r\nJay",
